Boil a #pot{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Peel and very finely chop the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and finely chopped). Slice the @red chilli{1}(sliced in half lengthways and finely chopped) in half lengthways and finely chop as much as you dare.

> Tip: Our chillis aren't actually that hot but add according to taste.

Chop the very top and bottom from the @courgette{1}. Slice the courgette lengthways into strips no thicker than ½ cm. Now slice the slices lengthways to make strands less than ½ cm thick.

> Tip: Really slice carefully to get thin linguine-like strands.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on low heat. Add the chilli and garlic and slowly cook for ~{2%minutes}.

> Tip: Make sure the heat is low so you do not burn the garlic.

Meanwhile add the @fettuccine{250%g} to the rapidly boiling water. Cook for ~{5%minutes} or until 'al dente'.

> Tip: 'Al dente' simply means it is cooked through but has a hint of firmness left in the middle.

While you are cooking the pasta add the courgette strips to the frying pan with the garlic and chilli, turn the heat to high and cook for ~{2-3%minutes} until the courgette slightly softens. Add @salt{1/4%tsp} and a few good grinds of @black pepper{a few grinds}.

> Tip: You want the courgette to stay slightly crunchy so don't overcook it.

When the pasta is 2 mins away from being cooked add in the @fresh peas{1/3%cup}. After 2 mins keep half a cup of the pasta water and drain the pasta and peas.

Add a couple of tbsp of pasta water to the courgette together with the @pesto{3%tbsp}. Toss everything together then add in the pasta and the peas. Toss all the ingredients together until everything is coated.

> Tip: Taste for seasoning and add a little more salt and pepper to taste.

Serve into bowls with a healthy sprinkling of @Pecorino cheese{2%tbsp}(grated). Now you're cooking!